WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.340
So I would like to--

00:00:05.260 --> 00:00:08.660
So today, I'm going to present an investigator-initiated trial

00:00:08.660 --> 00:00:11.040
led by my colleague, Dr. Ajay Noonkar,

00:00:11.040 --> 00:00:13.460
evaluating the role of belantemab, pomalidomide,

00:00:13.460 --> 00:00:16.560
and dexamethasone as maintenance therapy

00:00:16.560 --> 00:00:20.900
post-transplant and high-risk myeloma patients.

00:00:20.900 --> 00:00:23.800
These are my disclosures.

00:00:23.800 --> 00:00:26.760
So as we've heard over and over again in this conference,

00:00:26.760 --> 00:00:28.600
patients with high-risk disease have

00:00:28.600 --> 00:00:30.980
poor progression-free survival and overall survival

00:00:30.980 --> 00:00:33.040
as compared to standard-risk disease.

00:00:33.040 --> 00:00:37.220
The figure on the right here is from our RVD1000 data set.

00:00:37.220 --> 00:00:40.160
Long-term follow-up revealed a drastic difference

00:00:40.160 --> 00:00:42.940
in the median progression-free survival and overall survival

00:00:42.940 --> 00:00:45.340
in standard-risk disease versus high-risk.

00:00:45.340 --> 00:00:49.960
So this truly highlights an unmet need patient population.

00:00:49.960 --> 00:00:53.360
However, with modern-day therapies and induction

00:00:53.360 --> 00:00:56.560
approaches, it is now feasible to attain

00:00:56.560 --> 00:00:58.580
deep responses with high rates of MRD

00:00:58.580 --> 00:01:03.220
negativity in even the high-risk patient population.

00:01:03.220 --> 00:01:05.520
However, the master trial revealed

00:01:05.520 --> 00:01:09.540
that when patients with high-risk disease

00:01:09.540 --> 00:01:11.000
went on to the MRD--

00:01:11.000 --> 00:01:16.100
achieved MRD sure and went on to surveillance of treatment,

00:01:16.100 --> 00:01:19.580
the patients with more high-risk chromosomal abnormalities

00:01:19.580 --> 00:01:23.700
had a two-year incidence of progression of almost 47%,

00:01:23.700 --> 00:01:26.480
which tells us that fixed-duration therapy is

00:01:26.480 --> 00:01:28.560
probably not applicable to this group.

00:01:28.580 --> 00:01:31.620
So multiple different combination maintenance

00:01:31.620 --> 00:01:35.120
strategies have been explored in this patient population

00:01:35.120 --> 00:01:37.220
in the maintenance setting.

00:01:37.220 --> 00:01:40.700
We published our own experience with a triplet maintenance

00:01:40.700 --> 00:01:44.720
RVD a few years back, which revealed a median PFS

00:01:44.720 --> 00:01:47.340
of about 32 months in high-risk patients

00:01:47.340 --> 00:01:51.080
post-transplant or post-induction.

00:01:51.080 --> 00:01:55.820
Similarly, ELO RVD maintenance showed similar PFS rates.

00:01:55.820 --> 00:01:58.020
Cafirzomib and Revlimid maintenance was explored

00:01:58.020 --> 00:01:58.560
in the four days.

00:01:58.560 --> 00:02:02.180
We also published a daily trial, and it revealed a median PFS

00:02:02.180 --> 00:02:05.520
of about 42 months in the high-risk patient population.

00:02:05.520 --> 00:02:08.520
We also published our experience with KPD maintenance,

00:02:08.520 --> 00:02:11.880
Cafirzomib, Parm, and Dex, which showed actually

00:02:11.880 --> 00:02:15.660
a median PFS of 62 months, which is kind of unheard of

00:02:15.660 --> 00:02:18.160
in this high-risk patient population.

00:02:18.160 --> 00:02:21.280
And then other trials, like Optimum trial,

00:02:21.280 --> 00:02:24.240
and have been exploring other combination strategies

00:02:24.240 --> 00:02:28.540
with some promising responses.

00:02:28.540 --> 00:02:32.040
As my prior speakers, Dr. Martin and others,

00:02:32.040 --> 00:02:34.660
have already alluded to the DREAM study,

00:02:34.660 --> 00:02:36.400
the Algonquin study actually first

00:02:36.400 --> 00:02:40.120
evaluated this combination of Belantem and Parm/Dex

00:02:40.120 --> 00:02:44.500
and showed that this combination was safe and efficacious.

00:02:44.500 --> 00:02:46.100
And then these findings were further

00:02:46.100 --> 00:02:49.700
corroborated in the large phase III randomized control trial,

00:02:49.700 --> 00:02:52.240
the DREAM-8 study, where this combination was compared

00:02:52.240 --> 00:02:58.300
head-to-head with EVD or Parm/Velcate/Dex and showed pretty

00:02:58.300 --> 00:02:58.520
impressive results.

00:02:58.520 --> 00:03:00.500
So this was a very, very impressive study.

00:03:00.500 --> 00:03:05.300
It showed very impressive PFS rates of 71% at 12 months

00:03:05.300 --> 00:03:08.540
as compared to 51% in the standard of care arm.

00:03:08.540 --> 00:03:12.860
And this benefit was noted across all of the subgroups

00:03:12.860 --> 00:03:13.360
pretty much.

00:03:13.360 --> 00:03:15.900
And then, of course, as we heard,

00:03:15.900 --> 00:03:18.860
the major limitation in using Belantem/Parm/Velcate/Dex

00:03:18.860 --> 00:03:21.320
is the incidence of ocular toxicity.

00:03:21.320 --> 00:03:28.500
And in the DREAM-8 study, we basically saw that there was

00:03:28.500 --> 00:03:31.420
20 over 50 in about 34% of the patients.

00:03:31.420 --> 00:03:35.460
And 1% of the patient actually had worsening to 20 over 200.

00:03:35.460 --> 00:03:37.560
The median time to onset of this toxicity

00:03:37.560 --> 00:03:41.100
was about 112 days, which is about 16 weeks.

00:03:41.100 --> 00:03:43.260
And then the median duration of this toxicity

00:03:43.260 --> 00:03:46.380
was about four weeks, or 29 days.

00:03:46.380 --> 00:03:49.380
And the important point to note is that 90% of these patients

00:03:49.380 --> 00:03:52.600
actually had reversal of this toxicity.

00:03:52.600 --> 00:03:55.480
And I would like to highlight that the dose of Belantem/Parm/Velcate/Dex

00:03:55.480 --> 00:03:58.480
used in the DREAM-8 study was actually 2.5 milligrams per day.

00:03:58.480 --> 00:04:01.360
The dose of Belantem/Parm/Velcate/Dex

00:04:01.360 --> 00:04:04.900
was actually 1.9 milligrams per kilogram every four weeks

00:04:04.900 --> 00:04:05.860
for the first cycle.

00:04:05.860 --> 00:04:07.780
And then subsequently, it was a use

00:04:07.780 --> 00:04:13.080
at a dose of 1.9 milligrams per kilogram every four weeks.

00:04:13.080 --> 00:04:15.940
So this brings us to our IIT, where

00:04:15.940 --> 00:04:19.260
we use a combination of Belantem/Parm/Velcate/Dex

00:04:19.260 --> 00:04:22.060
in high-risk, newly diagnosed myeloma patients

00:04:22.060 --> 00:04:22.840
post-transplant.

00:04:22.840 --> 00:04:28.460
